notes.text:
This update for cpio fixes the following issues:
	  
- CVE-2019-14866: Fixed an improper validation of the values written 
  in the header of a TAR file through the to_oct() function which could 
  have led to unexpected TAR generation (bsc#1155199).

notes.text: In all versions of cpio before 2.13 does not properly validate input files when generating TAR archives. When cpio is used to create TAR archives from paths an attacker can write to, the resulting archive may contain files with permissions the attacker did not have or in paths he did not have access to. Extracting those archives from a high-privilege user without carefully reviewing them may lead to the compromise of the system.
